Status report of Yi Tong Tse on 1/29/99

This is the second week of writing code according to the schedule.
So far the following items have been done:

- finished main program and top level task routines.  The semaphores
  and data queues are correctly set up.

- the following data paths have been tested and are working for all
  EchoStar bitstreams:
      - live feed channel bypass path (with PID remap)
      - ad bitstream dropping path
      - other channel bypass path

- PES, ES header parsing to extract information used for splicing.
  At this time only big Endian is supported.

- created a test bitstream for DPI testing by muxing echo2 and echo3
  files into a single transport stream.


